# Style Guide

- Follow PEP 8 and PEP 257.
- Use type hints on all function signatures.
- Use Google-style docstrings and add them automatically when generating new functions/classes.
- Prefer explicit over implicit behavior (avoid magic values; avoid bare `except`).
- Do not silently swallow exceptions. Handle errors intentionally.
- Use `dataclasses` or `pydantic` models for structured data instead of raw `dict`s.
- Keep functions under 40 lines; extract helpers when logic grows.
- For any code touching external systems (HTTP, file I/O), keep responsibilities separated and easily mockable.

